The paper deals with the computation of simplicial depth, which is a concept in computational geometry and robust statistics. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also presents approximation algorithms, which suggests that it could be relevant to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). The use of Monte Carlo algorithms and the analysis of worst-case scenarios suggest that it could also be relevant to cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
